Use this tool to replace the `sorry` in the provided theorem with a potential proof.
The provided `proof_code` will replace the `sorry`, so should not contain the surrounding theorem
statement (it's read-only). It must be valid Lean 4 syntax. It cannot contain `sorry`; this will
be rejected. The tool will respond with the result of compiling the proof. If successful, then you may
finalize your response by returning the `theorem_proven` status. If unsuccessful, you can try again.
Note that each call to `update_proof` will completely replace the code provided in any previous
`update_proof`. Lemmas are unaffected.